  "term": "thm:liminf-smallest-subsequential-limit",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Liminf Is the Smallest Subsequential Limit",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(x_n)$ be a bounded real sequence, and let\n$I=\\liminf_{n\\to\\infty}x_n$. Then $I$ is a subsequential limit of\n$(x_n)$, and every subsequential limit of $(x_n)$ is greater than or\nequal to $I$.",
